IDirect3DViewport3 is an interface with additional methods compared to IDirect3DViewport2. If you're already implementing IDirect3DViewport2, then it is likely the issue lies with the order of your arguments within the CreateViewport method. Make sure to call IDirect3DDevice3::CreateViewport() with the correct parameters. In this case, you will pass in ID3D11Device3 (your device), D3D11_VIEWPORT (viewport as a D3D11_VIEWPORT structure), NULL, and D3D11_DEPTH_BUFFER_LAYOUT (depth buffer layout) as arguments. The return parameter is the IDirect3DViewport2. Hope this helps!

translation: Yes, that's accurate. The new methods are added at the end of the class definition. This allows developers to slowly adopt IDirectXObject2 by using IDirectXObject1 methods first and then gradually adding IDirectXObject2 methods.

With machine learning algorithms, we can now predict harms with greater accuracy, efficiency and speed than ever before.
